        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/petko147/{size}/42282_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-07-20T14:51:04.576Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Well, in my view, let the functionality to be the same as is now, in which when I leave the group, it post the message. Just add another option to silently leave group next to it, so in ancient old groups nobody is using, why someone needs to let all other people know that he is leaving? Nobody uses that group, it‚Äôs dead so why this spam has to occur? It then means, that I can‚Äôt leave a group when I don‚Äôt want to spam all people‚Ä¶ That‚Äôs bad, it doesn‚Äôt seems logical, this is security and privacy focused messenger, so definitely I want to have an ability to leave groups, but I don‚Äôt want to spam all people about it‚Ä¶</p>\n<p>And by the way, it doesn‚Äôt matter that much, that other people don‚Äôt know someone left, they can still verify if someone is there in the group members‚Ä¶ This privacy of being able to quietly remove from groups you don‚Äôt want to be in is much much more important for messenger like Signal is.</p>\n<p>So pleeeease, add this ability <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
