      {
        "id": 220331,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Herohtar",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-07-20T17:46:59.357Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Petko147\" data-post=\"11\" data-topic=\"48724\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/petko147/48/42282_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Petko147:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>old groups definitely can‚Äôt be destroyed</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Legacy groups (what I assume you mean by ‚Äúold groups‚Äù) don‚Äôt exist anymore; they can no longer be created and should have been forcibly upgraded to Groups V2 by now. If some managed to stick around, they almost certainly wouldn‚Äôt be usable and any changes Signal made related to groups wouldn‚Äôt apply to them.</p>\n<p>That being said, even Groups V2 don‚Äôt have any way to just delete the group. You have to kick everyone else out first (requires being admin), then leave it yourself.</p>\n<p>Does leaving a group really generate spam though? I know it creates a notice in the group, but does that notice bump the chat up in the list? I‚Äôm fairly certain it doesn‚Äôt cause the chat to show as having unread messages, but does it cause an actual notification from Signal?</p>",
        "post_number": 12,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 13,
